# ARCHON-IX | Environment Variables
# --------------------------------------------------------------
# The shipped site is static (Vite + GitHub Pages) and currently
# requires NO environment variables at runtime or build time.
#
# This file is intentionally safe to commit (.env is git-ignored)
# so that when a future server-side integration is added (for
# example a serverless proxy holding an LLM API key, or an Alchemy
# read key for live on-chain telemetry), collaborators know exactly
# which variables .env is expected to hold.
#
# When you add a real integration, append its variable below in the
# reserved section, then mirror the change in any deployment docs.
#
# Reserved for future hooks (DO NOT fill in real values here):
#   LLM_PROXY_URL=
#   ALCHEMY_API_KEY=
